    {
      "name": "ReleaseInfo",
      "docs": [
        "R6: authoritative facts returned by `chainpool.release_to_receiver` so the receiver",
        "does not re-parse the proof. This is a cross-program borsh ABI contract — its layout",
        "lives here (compile-time single source of truth) and any change requires both programs",
        "to be upgraded together (borsh rejects trailing/short bytes; no version negotiation).",
        "Fields carried as CPI accounts (bridge_mint, base_escrow) are validated by chainpool's",
        "own account constraints and are intentionally absent here; only data-only facts appear.",
        "2a: user = top-level to_address; dest_token = bridge_mint; min_amount_out = 0",
        "2b: user = inner.to_address; dest_token = inner.to_token; min_amount_out = inner.min"
      ],
      "type": {
        "kind": "struct",
        "fields": [
          {
            "name": "user",
            "type": "pubkey"
          },
